  "text": "The next concepts to be discussed in brief relates to human factors and ICT infrastructure. This section presents highlights of how human behavioral patterns and individual's acceptance or willingness to use educational technologies may influence social software adoption process in HEI. The study uses the following theories stated below to unravel the underlining the adoption models. The study will further focus on these theories of adoption as described in [46] , [CITATION_1] 's studies on ICT adoption models and approaches, namely the theory of reasoned action (TRA), theory of planned behavior (TPB), technology of acceptance model (TAM), technology readiness and acceptance model (TRAM) and self-determination theory will be discussed further in the study.",
